v080-0008: TTS CuTe DSL --wrap toolchain fix (applies on top of v080-0007)

Re-apply -Wl,--wrap=_cudaLaunchKernelEx at the qwen3_tts_inference executable
link. The Talker MLP CuTe DSL GEMM lives in the STATIC edgellmCore archive and
calls the runtime template wrapper _cudaLaunchKernelEx -> cudaLaunchKernelExC,
which no-ops on CUDA <12.8 for cuLibraryLoadData-loaded kernels (never registered
in fat-binary tables) -> "invalid device function" at launch. cmake/CuteDsl.cmake
applies the wrap only to its SHARED LINK_TARGETS; for the statically-linked
executable the wrap MUST be re-applied at the final link to redirect those call
sites to the shim's __wrap__cudaLaunchKernelEx (driver-API cuLaunchKernelEx).
No numerics change -- same kernel, correct launch path.

PROVEN EFFECT: without this, qwen3_tts_inference fails at the first Talker MLP GEMM
launch ("invalid device function") and emits zero audio. With it, the pipeline runs
end-to-end (en: 34 frames / 2.72s; zh: generates codes). This is the load-bearing
toolchain unblock.

DROPPED from the box-local 5ad0cbb commit (NOT included here):
  - projectToTalkerInput split-projection (role[:3]+body[3:3+N]): a speculative
    workaround for a CuTe GEMM row-1 corruption. Box testing + this verification
    confirm it has NO effect on the symptom (en still garbled, zh still EOS@2).
    Dropped to keep the tree clean (keep only changes with proven effect).
  - langId / 9-row CustomVoice conditioning + kernel layout: already tracked in
    v080-0007-customvoice-language-conditioning.patch. Not duplicated here.

This patch is incremental on top of v080-0007's shim block.

diff --git a/examples/omni/CMakeLists.txt b/examples/omni/CMakeLists.txt
index fd2086d..8539a62 100644
--- a/examples/omni/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/examples/omni/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -17,6 +17,19 @@ add_cross_build_link_options(qwen3_tts_inference)
 if(TARGET trt_edgellm_cutedsl_cudart_shim)
   target_link_libraries(qwen3_tts_inference PRIVATE
     "-Wl,--whole-archive" trt_edgellm_cutedsl_cudart_shim "-Wl,--no-whole-archive")
+  # The Talker MLP CuTe DSL GEMM (in the STATIC edgellmCore archive) calls the
+  # runtime template wrapper _cudaLaunchKernelEx, which forwards to
+  # cudaLaunchKernelExC. On CUDA <12.8 that host-side stub no-ops for
+  # cuLibraryLoadData-loaded kernels (they are never registered via fat-binary
+  # tables) -> "invalid device function" at launch. cute_dsl_setup() applies
+  # -Wl,--wrap only to its SHARED LINK_TARGETS; for a STATIC edgellmCore the
+  # wrap must be re-applied at the final executable link to redirect those call
+  # sites to the shim's __wrap__cudaLaunchKernelEx (driver-API cuLaunchKernelEx).
+  # No numerics change -- same kernel, correct launch path.
+  if(NOT DEFINED CUDA_CTK_VERSION OR CUDA_CTK_VERSION STREQUAL ""
+     OR CUDA_CTK_VERSION VERSION_LESS 12.8)
+    target_link_options(qwen3_tts_inference PRIVATE
+      "-Wl,--wrap=_cudaLaunchKernelEx")
+  endif()
 endif()

 # Set output directory
